No problem

The following is not working, you can't define defaults and types at the same time and with default `''` ts infers it as string and will complain about the passed parameter (since in most cases it is optional it can be `undefined`)

```ts
private dynamicRender(
  { key, fallback } = { key: '', fallback: '' },
) {
  return this.i18n.te(key) ? this.i18n.t(key).toString() : fallback;
}
```

So the only thing we can do is to move `?? ''` part into this function
```ts
private dynamicRender(
  { key, fallback }: { key: string; fallback: string; },
) {
  return this.i18n.te(key) ? this.i18n.t(key).toString() : fallback ?? '';
}
```

Hey @vasi26ro and @Joffcom ,
basically the issue here is that the way model fields are returned currently in the Odoo node makes it impossible for the node to know the value of the field. Here's what the structure looks like:
```json
{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": null,
  "result": {
    "display_name": {
      "type": "char",
      "required": false,
      "string": "Display Name"
    },
    "date": {
      "type": "date",
      "required": false,
      "string": "Date"
    }
  }
}
```

The issue with the current fields list is that it tries to find the name of the field by using `optionField.name` from the response payload. The thing is that `optionField.name` does not exist, thus why the `undefined`. (See https://github.com/n8n-io/n8n/blob/master/packages/nodes-base/nodes/Odoo/Odoo.node.ts#L124 for more details)

